Text.SourceString: Is that… Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=surprised>Wow! I almost didn’t recognize you in that getup.//<portrait=normal>Oh, so you’re the one moving into the lot, huh? That would explain the outfit.
Right. It’s not just the town, you know. The inn isn’t as busy as it used to be.//Hopefully, with you moving in…it’s a sign of something good.
Oh, hello there. It's good to see you here.
...//Is there something you needed from me?
People like to dismiss things they can't see.//What's the fun in that?
Being alone isn't always bad.//Personal space is rarely a thing when you grow up with someone <Italic>sparkly</> like <NPCName>Suki</>.
Sure, energetic works too.
I sometimes wonder if running this inn is the right move for me.//I don't know...
Ah, here comes Monday…
*yawn*
Is everything okay?
<NPCName>Suki</> and I divide our workload.//I get the weekday shift, and she covers the weekend.
It’s pretty fair, I think… Right?
We keep track of guests daily and run an analysis at the end of the season.//That's how we're taught by our parents.
The mayor is always watching the economy.//He gets excited about the analysis when we go over what we learned in the past season and all that.
The inn usually gets more guests during festivals.
<NPCName>Suki</> and I divide our workload.//I get the weekday shift, and she covers the weekend.

It’s pretty fair, I think… Right?//<portrait=sad>Maybe she doesn’t see it that way...//<portrait=sad>I mean, she does a lot of the cooking, but she doesn’t seem to mind. So don’t you think that’s fair?
One of my hobbies is definitely reading!//What about you? What do you like to do in your spare time?
Another good hobby is having meaningful discussions. Pick each other’s brains and share views…//You learn a lot of new things that way.
I’ve got a few tips for you. I’ve lived by the beach my whole life, so I know that sometimes you can find rare seashells.//<portrait=happy>I’m talking rare as in expensive!
Yeah! There are plenty of rare, pretty shells on our beach. Kids love collecting them.
I’m pretty much free today. I usually pay the bills on Wednesdays…//That way, I can make sure that we don’t double pay.
Think of it this way, the more people that are allowed access to paying the bills, the more chance that there’ll be mistakes – overpaying, missing invoices, all that.
Our kitchen is free to use! It’s included in the room rate.//<portrait=normal>Guests can use our kitchen and anything we put out in the lobby.//But you knew that. You stayed in our inn that summer.
It’s nice to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I’ve got a few tips for you. I’ve lived by the beach my whole life, so I know that sometimes you can find rare seashells.//<portrait=happy>I’m talking rare as in expensive!
Yeah! There are plenty of rare, pretty shells on our beach. Kids love collecting them.
Neither <NPCName>Suki</> nor I knew what to do when we first started running Coral Inn. Ha ha. But yeah, it takes a lot to run an inn.//I’m sure it’s nothing compared to running a farm, though.
How’s your week been so far?
Ha ha! It IS Monday. Too early to tell, huh?
I <Italic>did</> take some questionable courses in university.//<portrait=normal>But actually, those classes were the most fun. Looking back, that should have been my major.
I’m sure I’m not the first person who picked the wrong major, though.//<portrait=annoyed>By the way, who told you all this?
How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Here’s a way to improve the community. The library should get more books about extraterrestrial life.
…Just saying. Some people are interested in that stuff, you know.
Uh-uh. Not just me… Let me see… Hmm… <NPCName>Noah</>…and, um…
I don’t think we’re alone in the universe…//I’ve read some interesting theories.
Can you imagine what life is like on Mars? I would love to go there and see it for myself.
If you’re not a caffeine person, a quick jog does the trick when you need to wake up.
I don’t think we’re alone in the universe…//I’ve read some interesting theories.
Can you imagine what life is like on Mars? I would love to go there and see it for myself.
Here’s a way to improve the community. The library should get more books about extraterrestrial life.
…Just saying. Some people are interested in that stuff, you know.
Uh-uh. Not just me… Let me see… Hmm… <NPCName>Noah</>…and, um…
I’m not doing anything today.//<portrait=happy>Fun, fun!

There is this magnificent rainbow seashell one time that <NPCName>Valentina</> brought home.//<portrait=surprised>Have you seen one of those?//<portrait=normal>Oh, it was so beautiful. I’m pretty sure it would sell for a lot too.
Just keep in mind that if you like collecting seashells, keep an eye out for them at the beach!
Here’s a way to improve the community. The library should get more books about extraterrestrial life.
…Just saying. Some people are interested in that stuff, you know.
Uh-uh. Not just me… Let me see… Hmm… <NPCName>Noah</>…and, um…
Sometimes we dye our sheets different colors to brighten things up…//That way they look new.
It’s all <NPCName>Suki</>’s idea, to tell you the truth.//<portrait=normal>If it were up to me, I’d just leave the sheets beige.
Hello, <PlayerName>$player</>! What brings you here?
When we were kids, <NPCName>Suki</> and I used to dress the same to confuse our friends. It didn’t always work, because we aren’t identical, but when it did, it was great!
The 10-year-old me was much more adventurous than adult me.//Now, I like to keep things plain and beige.
The universe is so big, don’t you think?//<portrait=happy>I mean, look at Earth. We haven’t even fully explored it yet.

We seem to keep finding new species of animals… On land, in the ocean! Ancient fish. Gosh.//<portrait=surprised>What else is out there?!//<portrait=happy>Could there be life on other planets? I think so.
I could be wrong… But I’m keeping my mind open.//<portrait=happy>Let’s see where it gets me.
I don’t see why I should buy my own camera.//I don't want to spend money on a camera when I can just borrow <NPCName>Macy</>’s.
Ah, she doesn’t mind anyway. Besides, it’s not like I use it every day…//<portrait=surprised>Maybe three times a year, tops!
Sometimes we dye our sheets different colors to brighten things up…
It’s all <NPCName>Suki</>’s idea, to tell you the truth.//<portrait=normal>If it were up to me, I’d just leave the sheets beige.
Morning jogs can be fun, especially with a partner.//Don’t brush it off just yet. Give it a try!
You could say that about pretty much anything, though, huh?
I don’t see why I should buy my own camera.//I don't want to spend money on a camera when I can just borrow <NPCName>Macy</>’s.
Ah, she doesn’t mind anyway. Besides, it’s not like I use it every day… Maybe three times a year, tops!
As soon as <NPCName>Suki</> was back in town, our parents decided to retire early. They didn’t think the inn had enough work for four people.
You see, my sis used to live in Labuan Bajo, the little town on the other side of Coral Island, with her ex-husband. But since the, errr, separation, she moved back here.
The internet has way too many poorly sourced articles about flying saucers… Hmm…
It’s a bit hard to sort through them all. If only there were a filter that showed just certain publications…
<NPCName>Rafael</>? Yeah, he might be at the inn today.//He does visit us on Sunday when he can.
He sure is dedicated. <NPCName>Rafael</> visits <NPCName>Valentina</> on weekends and makes sure she’s all right.
As soon as <NPCName>Suki</> was back in town, our parents decided to retire early. They didn’t think the inn had enough work for four people.
You see, my sis used to live in Labuan Bajo, the little town on the other side of Coral Island, with her ex-husband. But since the, errr, separation, she moved back here.
The cherry blossoms look beautiful this time of year.
This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…
Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?
This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…
Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?
Ah… I kinda miss the snow already.
On my morning walk the other day, I saw people gathering bamboo shoots near the lake.//You should check it out.
Are you planning on planting pineapples this Summer?
They’re all right. I was just curious…//But I heard that <NPCName>Joko</> loves pineapples. One time he gave us some as a souvenir from his trip.
I’m so happy Spring is almost over, because it means Summer is right around the corner. I love the longer days!
There’s something cheerful about the flowers in Spring. I know <NPCName>Suki</> can’t get enough of them.
I’m glad I made it through another Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now I can look forward to Summer!
I’m just counting the days until Summer is here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I don’t usually love the color pink, but I make an exception for cherry blossoms.//<portrait=happy>They’re just so beautiful.

Living with <NPCName>Suki</> in Spring has pros and cons.//<portrait=happy>Pro: I barely have to clean anything, because she goes on a cleaning spree.//<portrait=annoyed>Con: She’s even more overbearing and annoying than usual.
Summer, finally! Now I can read outside as much as I want.
Do you know what Summer is good for? Spending time outside, eating tons of minced jackfruit pies, going to the beach – all that good stuff.
I’ll read anywhere, but there’s something about reading outside in the Summer sun that’s more relaxing.
Easily the best thing about Summer is the abundance of jackfruit. I can make as many minced jackfruit pies as I want!
I’m excited about the Beach Cleanup Festival later this season. Are you?
It’s easier to do my…research in Summer.//I can stay out longer to see if there’s anything strange on the island.
It’s nice to see the community come together. It’s one of the reasons I love the Beach Cleanup Festival.
I wish <NPCName>Noah</> would come to the forest with me to help with my research, but he just wants to stay at the beach all day.
I love seeing the daisies popping up everywhere. It practically screams Summer.
Why can’t Summer be longer? I haven’t finished my reading yet!
It’s the last week of Fall, and do you know what that means?//<portrait=annoyed>We have to prepare the inn for Winter. Ugh.
Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Now, if only it were a bit warmer…
Brrrr. It’s starting to get cold. I’ll have to do my reading inside soon.
I miss Summer already…
It’s so chilly…
When will this Winter be over?
The only good thing about Winter is it’s when our birthday is.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything else I can do without.

I asked my parents <Italic>and</> <NPCName>Suki</> if we could just close the inn for Winter, but they shot me down. Many times.//<portrait=annoyed>You think a broken air conditioner is a problem, wait until you deal with a guest complaining about the heater.
I’d close the inn all Winter if it were up to me. But we can’t. Something about being the only inn in town. Ugh.
I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival. It’s so fun and festive, but it also means Winter is officially over.
It can be a bit of a bummer to have a birthday so close to a festival, but our parents made sure we didn’t feel left out when we were younger.
The snow is pretty, I’ll admit. But does it have to be so cold?
If I ever leave this town, the festival would be one thing that I’d miss.
I love seeing all these pretty Summer flowers around the island.//Diversity is beautiful, isn’t it?
Make sure to use enough sunscreen for the beach cleanup tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be in the sun the whole day.
There’s a swimming contest too.//<NPCName>Sunny’s</> going to be the winner again, I bet. Ha ha!
Ah, the beach looks so clean. But I hope we don’t forget there’s still so much trash in the sea and the river.//We still need to change our lifestyle to stop this from happening.
Everyone did such a great job yesterday.
I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left on his trip yet…
I should head to <NPCName>Ben’s</> next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.
The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.
I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do that?
I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…
They give out free mooncakes at the Harvest Festival.//They’re <NPCName>Betty’s</>, so they’re good, for sure!
<NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</> are very talented. They made some of our cabinets.//I wonder how long it took them to get so good at carpentry.
<NPCName>Noah</> wanted to open a booth with the information we gathered on flying saucers.
Nope! I’m not doing that. Thankfully, he changed his mind.
The inn got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the broken heater in their room. So we have to make sure it’s working this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.
I had my green tea too late today.//<portrait=sad>I don’t think I’ll be able to sleep tonight…
I couldn’t get to sleep until 1 am. I might have had too much caffeine yesterday.
I like dinner parties, but sometimes people can wear you out…
Is it too early to say Happy New Year?
This weather makes me sleepy…
This weather makes me sleepy…
Meh… A little rain is fine with me…
I see you don’t mind it either…
*<NPCName>Alice</> is ignoring you*
Quite a storm, isn’t it?
I hope it doesn’t turn into a storm like last time! We can’t afford to install a new heating system every Winter.
If this Winter gets any colder, I’m afraid we’ll start losing business.
…I hope it doesn’t get to that point.
I’m going to put all the extra blankets up front. In case any of our guests need one.
Do you need a room?
*<NPCName>Alice</> seems to be working*
I just updated our point-of-sale system. Let’s see how it works!
I’m a little busy right now…
I’m gonna get ready for bed, then read for a bit…
We offer wine in the evening and a fresh fruit bar in the morning…//<portrait=happy>I think that should be enough, don’t you?
Someone on the internet named Sarahhh with three H’s said that she loved the inn! And couldn’t wait to come back.
Just trying to respond to online reviewers. Then I’m going to manage our social media marketing.
Don’t even try to tell <NPCName>Suki</> to sit still and work the desk for too long.//She won’t be able to do it.
<NPCName>Suki</>’s too active for a desk job.
I think it may be a good idea to rent out sales space in the lobby.
I meant, like, <NPCName>Luke</>  for instance. He could rent some space over there, by the door, and sell electronics.
Or – oh! The vineyard! They could sell wine here.
Looking for one of our guests, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>You don’t need my permission. Go ahead and find them.
Thanks for asking, though.
Sorry, I can’t open any locked doors for you. If it’s closed, there’s nothing I can help you with.//I guess my best advice is just to talk to the guest.
Once you get to know them better, maybe they’ll let you in their room.
Yes? I don’t want to be rude, but I’m a little too tired to chat…
Did you just have your morning walk too? I like how quiet it is in the morning.//Right before everyone wakes up. It’s just you and the birds.
I have to work today. I’m going straight to the inn after this.
<NPCName>Karen</> used to have a room at the inn before she rented that space over there.
I didn’t know then that she was going to install drills around the island…//She was always very secretive. Never really looked like a tourist, either.
Did you hear about the light phenomenon over on Turtle Island?
I do like to read about odd phenomena all over the world.//<portrait=surprised>It fascinates me.
Fancy meeting you here!//<portrait=happy>I only ever see <NPCName>Ben</> and sometimes a monkey or two.
Are you heading to the cavern?
Hmm… I think I’ll walk through town on my way home.//<portrait=normal>I have to make a quick stop at the library.
My granddad told me that his friend saw a bright green light deep in the forest. He was pretty sure it was an alien spaceship.
Could be nothing, but who knows…//<portrait=normal>I might see something one of these days and decide for myself.
It’s such a different vibe in here compared to the inn.
Some people have claimed to see a figure over the lake…//<portrait=happy>The elders call it the Goddess…
…What if…//<portrait=annoyed>What if she’s not a spiritual figure like the locals believe, but actually from another planet?!
If you're interested in alien, you should read this book by Professor Kiep.//He has interesting theories about ET intelligence. I read it back in university...
Who orders the books inside the library, I wonder?//There are way too many cookbooks.
I wonder if the library has any new books. I’ve been reading the same old books.
I’m not being fair. It’s my own fault because I like to reread the same old books.
Can you smell the salt? Hmmm…
I’ll head back to the inn soon. I just wanna get some new books first at the library.
Would I? I would love to
Yesss, yes I do.//Where should we get married?
That sounds exciting, I can't wait
Can't waitt
That is my dream
I'm sorry, I prefer we just stay friends
Don't you think we need a little more time?
I wish we always stay together forever
